<item>
            <title>[SOLR-11425] SolrClientBuilder does not allow infinite timeout (value 0)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-11425</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/lucene-solr/blob/master/solr/solrj/src/java/org/apache/solr/client/solrj/impl/SolrClientBuilder.java#L53&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;org.apache.solr.client.solrj.impl.SolrClientBuilder#withConnectionTimeout&lt;/a&gt; does not allow to set the value of 0 which means infinite timeout, but &lt;a href=&quot;https://hc.apache.org/httpcomponents-client-ga/httpclient/apidocs/org/apache/http/client/config/RequestConfig.html#getConnectTimeout()&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;RequestConfig&lt;/a&gt; where it will be used have the option to do so.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13106375">SOLR-11425</key>
            <summary>SolrClientBuilder does not allow infinite timeout (value 0)</summary>
