                            <comment id="16195039" author="elyograg" created="Fri, 6 Oct 2017 19:00:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can understand the instinct that led the design to exclude a value of zero, and even though infinite timeouts can be problematic, I think the patch for this issue is a good change &amp;#8211; it&apos;s not our job to enforce a finite timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I do wonder if perhaps the javadoc should have a note about zero being an infinite timeout, which could result in client operations that never return.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
